{
  "page": "King's Gate",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the gate of the Red Keep, see <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Gate_(Red_Keep)\" title=\"King&#39;s Gate (Red Keep)\">King's Gate (Red Keep)</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kings_landing_map.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/4/46/Kings_landing_map.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kings_landing_map.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>1 <a href=\"/index.php/Rosby_road\" title=\"Rosby road\">Rosby road</a>, 2 <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_Gate\" title=\"Dragon Gate\">Dragon Gate</a>, 3 <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Gate\" title=\"Iron Gate\">Iron Gate</a>, 4 <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a>, 5 <a href=\"/index.php/Shae%27s_manse\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shae&#39;s manse\">Shae's manse</a>, 6 <a href=\"/index.php/Chataya%27s_brothel\" title=\"Chataya&#39;s brothel\">Chataya's brothel</a>, 7 <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Gate\" title=\"Old Gate\">Old Gate</a>, 8 <a href=\"/index.php/Flea_Bottom\" title=\"Flea Bottom\">Flea Bottom</a>, 9 <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>, 10 <a href=\"/index.php/Street_of_the_Sisters\" title=\"Street of the Sisters\">Street of the Sisters</a>, 11 <a href=\"/index.php/Gate_of_the_Gods\" title=\"Gate of the Gods\">Gate of the Gods</a>, 12 <a href=\"/index.php/Cobbler%27s_Square\" title=\"Cobbler&#39;s Square\">Cobbler's Square</a>, 13 <a href=\"/index.php/Guildhall_of_the_Alchemists\" title=\"Guildhall of the Alchemists\">Guildhall of the Alchemists</a>, 14 <a href=\"/index.php/Hook\" title=\"Hook\">Hook</a>, 15 <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>, 16 <a href=\"/index.php/Muddy_Way\" title=\"Muddy Way\">Muddy Way</a>, 17 <a href=\"/index.php/Fishmonger%27s_Square\" title=\"Fishmonger&#39;s Square\">Fishmonger's Square</a>, 18 <a href=\"/index.php/River_Gate\" title=\"River Gate\">River Gate</a>, 19 <a href=\"/index.php/Shop_of_Tobho_Mott\" title=\"Shop of Tobho Mott\">Tobho Mott's shop</a>, 20 <a href=\"/index.php/Street_of_Steel\" title=\"Street of Steel\">Street of Steel</a>, 21 <a href=\"/index.php/Harbor_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Harbor of King&#39;s Landing\">harbor</a>, 22 <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a>, 23 <a href=\"/index.php/River_Row\" title=\"River Row\">River Row</a>, 24 <a href=\"/index.php/Fish_market\" title=\"Fish market\">fish market</a>, 25 <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_grounds_(King%27s_Landing)\" title=\"Tourney grounds (King&#39;s Landing)\">tourney grounds</a>, <b>26 King's Gate</b>, 27 <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsroad\" title=\"Kingsroad\">kingsroad</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>King's Gate</b> is one of the seven huge gates along the city walls of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The King's Gate is by the southern corner of the southwest wall of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, connecting the western end of the <a href=\"/index.php/River_Row\" title=\"River Row\">River Row</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_grounds_(King%27s_Landing)\" title=\"Tourney grounds (King&#39;s Landing)\">tourney grounds</a> outside the city by the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Rush\" title=\"Blackwater Rush\">Blackwater Rush</a>. There is a sally port in it,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and a stable near it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Heads of the condemned can be mounted on spikes above the King's Gate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_19_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">19&#160;AC</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> decreed that new city walls with seven gates, each with a massive gatehouse and defensive towers, be built to protect <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Gawen\" title=\"Gawen\">Gawen</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Osmund_Strong\" title=\"Osmund Strong\">Osmund Strong</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, headed the construction, which took place between <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_20_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">20</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_26_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">26&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthree_heads_had_the_dragon_-_governance_under_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthree_heads_had_the_dragon_-_governance_under_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a> had his own wife and queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Harroway\" title=\"Alys Harroway\">Alys Harroway</a>, tortured to death and executed. Following her death, Alys's body was cut into seven parts and mounted on spikes above each of the seven gates of the city, one of which was above the King's Gate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maegor_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Aerea_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerea Targaryen\">Aerea Targaryen</a> spent part of the regency of <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> working in a stable near the King's Gate, which she considered to be the happiest time of her life.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloaks\">gold cloaks</a> at the King's Gate fled amid the <a href=\"/index.php/Riot_of_King%27s_Landing_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Riot of King&#39;s Landing (Dance of the Dragons)\">riot of King's Landing</a>. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Perkin_the_Flea\" title=\"Perkin the Flea\">Perkin the Flea</a> recruited scores of former gold cloaks during the <a href=\"/index.php/Moon_of_the_Three_Kings\" title=\"Moon of the Three Kings\">Moon of the Three Kings</a>, and he gained control over the King's Gate, the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_Gate\" title=\"Dragon Gate\">Dragon Gate</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/Trystane_Truefyre\" title=\"Trystane Truefyre\">Trystane Truefyre</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regency of Aegon III</a>, the King's Hand, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tyland_Lannister\" title=\"Tyland Lannister\">Tyland Lannister</a> ordered the city gates to be strengthened so they could better resist attacks from within the city walls.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> led his <a href=\"/index.php/Northmen\" title=\"Northmen\">northmen</a> through the King's Gate during the <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Sack of King&#39;s Landing\">Sack of King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kings_Gate.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/53/Kings_Gate.jpg/350px-Kings_Gate.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/53/Kings_Gate.jpg/525px-Kings_Gate.jpg 1.5x, /images/5/53/Kings_Gate.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kings_Gate.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The King's Gate, by Bjarne Hansen © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>After leaving a riverside evening feast during the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand%27s_tourney\" title=\"Hand&#39;s tourney\">Hand's tourney</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a> climb in a cart near the King's Gate and are taken through <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following the death of King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a> and ascension of King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a>, travelers are only allowed to depart <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Gate\" title=\"Iron Gate\">Iron Gate</a> or the King's Gate, both of which are manned by <a href=\"/index.php/Red_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Red cloaks\">red cloaks</a>. Spying from the rooftop of an inn by the King's Gate, <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> watches the guards search wagons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> prevents the <a href=\"/index.php/Northmen\" title=\"Northmen\">northmen</a> who escort Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Cleos_Frey\" title=\"Cleos Frey\">Cleos Frey</a> to King's Landing from entering the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> When Tyrion sends Cleos back to <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, the northmen rejoin him at the King's Gate for the journey west.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After ships land by the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_grounds_(King%27s_Landing)\" title=\"Tourney grounds (King&#39;s Landing)\">tourney grounds</a>, the gate is assaulted with a battering ram by the army of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> rides to the King's Gate, where the gatehouse square is littered with wounded. Sandor refuses to lead a sortie and instead deserts from the battle. Tyrion and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Mandon_Moore\" title=\"Mandon Moore\">Mandon Moore</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> instead lead a detachment out of a sally port. After ending the threat of the ram, they ride toward the <a href=\"/index.php/River_Gate\" title=\"River Gate\">River Gate</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Osney_Kettleblack\" title=\"Osney Kettleblack\">Osney Kettleblack</a> later reports that the King's Gate is again being rammed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a> meets his betrothed, <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, at the King's Gate when she arrives at King's Landing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Tyrion finds mud, ash, and bones when he investigates the land outside of the King's Gate. He reports to his father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, that the gate is splintered and should be replaced.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> is sent by his sister, Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, to inspect the city gates. According to him the King's Gate needs to be replaced.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Jaremy</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> gave us a splendid choice. <a href=\"/index.php/Take_the_black\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Take the black\">Take the black</a>, or see our heads on spikes before evenfall. No offense intended, Tyrion.<br /><b>Tyrion</b>: None taken, Ser Jaremy. My father is very fond of spiked heads, especially those of people who have annoyed him in some fashion. And a face as noble as yours, well, no doubt he saw you decorating the city wall above the King's Gate. I think you would have looked very striking up there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jaremy_Rykker\" title=\"Jaremy Rykker\">Jaremy Rykker</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Even so, by the time they reached the King's Gate, he could hear a booming crash of wood on wood that told him the battering ram had been brought into play. The groaning of the great hinges sounded like the moans of a dying <a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">giant</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Nothing remained beyond the King's Gate but mud and ashes and bits of burned bone, yet already there were people living in the shadow of the city walls, and others selling fish from barrows and barrels.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Gate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_59\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 59\">Chapter 59</a>, Tyrion XIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, A Surfeit of Rulers.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Triumphant.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_21\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 21\">Chapter 21</a>, Tyrion III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"